<div1 type="letter">

<pb facs="nei.j4a.2.3-4_0001" />
 
<fw type="curatorial">3</fw>

<fw type="letterhead">
   SYLVANIA
   <lb/>
 BARRYTOWN-ON-HUDSON
</fw>
<opener>
<dateline>June 1: 1911</dateline>
   
   
<salute>My dear Mr. Neihardt,</salute>
</opener>
   <p>Well, I am just delighted to get your note; &amp; I thank you for writing it.</p>

   <p>My books are not the sort that get the most popular applause in this particular age. <del/><add>I</add> often long to transfer them to some other age &amp; see if they wouldn't
   
   <pb facs="nei.j4a.2.3-4_0002"/>
   <fw type="curatorial">4</fw>
  
   go better.</p>

   <p>With all the philosophy in the world there remains sometimes a doubt as to whether one hasn't really failed in the true sense of failure &amp; written what really isn't especially valuable anyway &#8212; and perhaps <add>is</add> never to be discovered at all. I confess your letter gives me infinite pleasure.</p>
   <closer>
   <salute>Yours kindly &amp; gratefully</salute>
   
   <signed>John Jay Chapman</signed>
   </closer>

</div1>
</body>

